Most of the observed features can be interpreted in the framework of\nnon-axisymmetric magnetospheric accretion. We consider two possible models. In\nthe first the asymmetry is induced by orbital motion of an invisible, low mass\nsecondary, which also influences the gasflows around the star, the second\nconsiders rotational modulation of a single star with an inclined or asymmetric\nmagnetosphere.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Feb 2001 12:52:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-06"}
